doc_summary_long: SC official suggested his employees commit suicide if they are unhappy An official in Richland County, South Carolina, is under fire for making an appalling comment during a staff meeting, WSOC reported. Several emergency medical service workers said Assistant County Administrator Kevin Bronson suggested his employees commit suicide if they are unhappy, after some complained about work conditions.
